data.content:
**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>`.** Both work without requiring an `unsafe` context — you can write:

```csharp
Span<nint>  signed   = stackalloc nint[4];
Span<nuint> unsigned = stackalloc nuint[4];
```

On this 64-bit system, each element is 8 bytes. The only caveat is that `sizeof(nint)` requires `unsafe` — use `IntPtr.Size` instead if you need the size in safe code.
